name: ADOX PAN-X B/W Reversal 100ASA Super 8 Film
description:
ADOX PAN-X Reverso Super8 is a true reversal B&W film which can be run in any Super8 projector right after developing. It is our alternative for those seeking a replacement for the discontinued Kodak Plus-X. We gave PAN-X Reverso everything a Super8 reversal film could possibly get: • A forgiving, silver rhich emulsion which does not block off in the highlights and features full shadow detail if exposed to 100 ASA. • A DMAX of above 3,0 (depending on the developer used). • An anti halation layer between the base and the emulsion yielding crips images and finest details even at high magnification factors. • A clear triacetate base fpr brilliant projection. PAN-X Reverso is perforated on an entirely refurbished step-perforator which punches 4 holes, advances the film, positions the last 4 holes with catching pins and then repunches again with an accuracy of 2/100mm over the row of 8 holes. This accuracy sets a new standard and your frames stay steady as a rock. Our film cassette is using a plane pressure plate for exact positioning of the film. 15 meters of Super8 film for about 3 minutes and 20 seconds of fun. Standard developing in Kodak D-94A process.
Postage Prices: UK: £3 for first film & 35p for each additional film. Rest of World: £3.50 for first film & £2 for each additional film.

name: Fomapan R100 B/W Reversal 100ASA Super 8 Film
description:
Fomapan R100 is now available in Super 8mm Cartridges to fit all high-end Super 8mm cameras.This film is characterized by very good differentiation of fine gray shades both in areas of highlights and shadows, giving a very high contrast film noir look. Each Box comes with one 50ft. foil-sealed Cartridge, processing instructions, and a list of labs that process the film. If you'd like to try something different than Kodak, try Fomapan R100. Custom loaded in the US by Spectra on behalf of L.S Moses.

name: Super 8 Processing
description:
We finally have a processing service in place so that you can now get your film, processing and soon telecine all in the same place. We can offer processing for all of the film that we sell except B/W Negative and Fomapan stock - we hope the we will be able to offer these very soon though. Just select the processing option your film requires from the options below.
When sending your film for processing please make sure that you print off and include either your order confirmation email or Paypal invoice. If this is not possible, please make sure you include a note with at very least your name and return address. This is simply so we can return your order easily. Film is sent to the lab every Wednesday. For film to be sent to the lab that week it needs to be with us by then so we can send it out that day. Film is returned to us approx. every 3 weeks. Please allow a few extras days for you to receive your film.
Please send your film to out to the address listed on the contact page.
Postage Prices: Shipping prices below are inclusive of return postage from the lab. UK: 90p for first film & 35p for each additional film. Rest of World: £3.50 for first film & £2 for each additional film.
